The paper deals with coding theory and the construction of matrices for transmitting over slow fading channels, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also uses properties of Hasse derivatives, which are commonly used in algebraic coding theory, and has connections to Reed-Solomon codes, Reed-Muller codes, and repeated-root cyclic codes, which are all topics in coding theory and could potentially place the paper in the data structures (cs.DS), distributed computing (cs.DC), cryptography (cs.CR), or social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
